Providers\">All in One Payment Service Providers<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/using-modern-payment-types-securely\/#payment-gateways-for-online-sales\" title=\"Payment Gateways for Online Sales\">Payment Gateways for Online Sales<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/using-modern-payment-types-securely\/#do-modern-payment-types-come-embedded-with-corresponding-security-features\" title=\"Do Modern Payment Types Come Embedded with Corresponding Security Features?\">Do Modern Payment Types Come Embedded with Corresponding Security Features?<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/using-modern-payment-types-securely\/#secure-transactions-while-evading-modern-complexity-of-payments\" title=\"Secure Transactions While Evading Modern Complexity of Payments\">Secure Transactions While Evading Modern Complexity of Payments<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-payment-ecosystem-and-its-attributes\"><\/span>The Payment Ecosystem and Its Attributes<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>New technology and various acquisitions and mergers have given rise to novel payment types, playing a significant role in the business sector. These platforms have partnered with traditional financial providers to cater to the latest merchant and customer preferences.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While they enable businesses to manage finances, <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/5-step-guide-to-secure-online-card-payments\/\">contemporary methods<\/a> have increased the complexity of payments and security concerns.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To learn how to use modern payment types securely, you\u2019ll first understand this landscape\u2019s ecosystem. During transaction scenarios, various players interact to process the payment cycle. These include;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Issuers<\/li><li>Acquirers<\/li><li>Payment facilitators<\/li><li>Card networks<\/li><li>Payment gateways<\/li><li>Payment processors<\/li><li>Value-added resellers<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><br>Recently, these players, alongside others, have helped transform the payment ecosystem by creating alternative channels for merchants and their consumers. Aided by some key drivers, incumbent financial providers willing to exploit emerging markets have to find solutions for insecurity and other complexity of payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Several drivers which create incentives to attain these solutions include the need for;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-availability-of-real-time-payments\"><\/span>The Availability of Real-Time Payments<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Speed, messaging capabilities, and instant availability of transaction status add value to this new phase of payment type\u2019s evolution. Such features make the difference between traditional and current types or platforms. They provide businesses with features or functionality to meet customer demand through innovation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"blockchain-and-distributed-ledger-technology-dlt\"><\/span>Blockchain and Distributed Ledger Technology DLT<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Among other attributes, Blockchain changes the processing cost models of financial transactions, including new payment types. The secure DLT enables processes to be carried out over <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/electronic-funds-transfer-benefits-security-cost\/\">distributed system networks<\/a> like the cloud. That limits the usage of costly and often vulnerable mainframes and data centers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"influences-of-external-nonphysical-interfaces\"><\/span>Influences of External Nonphysical Interfaces<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Classic payment interfaces and their developed solutions have fallen out of grace due to challenges by external stakeholders. Two essential factors contributing to this are Virtual Reality and voice assistants by Google, Amazon, Apple, and Facebook.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>mage recognition and natural language processors or NLPs enhance this functionality, ensuring the long-term relevance of nonphysical solutions towards new payment types.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-vision-of-a-unified-platform\"><\/span>The Vision of a Unified Platform<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Unified Payments System or UPI does away with Visa, MasterCard, or SWIFT payment systems launched in 2016. Various types of new payments can integrate easily to capture more of the mobile space using the open-source platform.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s essentially the launching pad for what\u2019s touted as a single payment base that does away with the current oversaturation of providers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-are-the-modern-payment-types-and-their-security-shortcomings\"><\/span>What Are the Modern Payment Types and Their Security Shortcomings?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>New payment types proliferate and get adopted along with the increase in technology-driven commerce models. Leading modern transaction solutions include unattended checkout, social commerce, and cross-channel acceptance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Important contributing factors include ease of use, less friction, and speed, meaning businesses increase profits and reduce the complexity of payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, your customer-facing business is measured by how you can deliver a seamless shopping experience. The internet, especially with the onset of high 4G and 5G bandwidths, drives digital and e-wallets, plus their subsets mobile pay.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Less traditional payment types posing security risks have opted to improve their infrastructure or risk obscurity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, Europay, MasterCard, and Visa created a standard for smart payment cards with superior security called EMV. These cards contain a chip that\u2019s read when inserted into a reader instead of the magnetic strip versions vulnerable to fraud.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data on these chips is encrypted and constantly changes to make it challenging for fraudsters without sophisticated technology to extract anything valuable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"how-do-you-implement-secure-modern-payment-types\"><\/span>How Do You Implement Secure Modern Payment Types?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Monitoring your financial security will depend on the types of payments you accept. It would help set up non-cash transactions using modern digital payment types. These also offer ease of tracking your sales and inventory, seeing as there\u2019s no math error and less time is spent adding up receipts and records.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In-person card payments remain the most secure, seeing as the risk of fraud and chargebacks is reduced. But Near Field Communication or NFC payment platforms like Apple or Google Pay have <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/international-payments-local-vs-digital-banking\/\">dynamic encryption<\/a> to increase user security. Other essential areas to streamline when using modern payment types securely include;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"an-account-with-reputable-merchant-services\"><\/span>An account with Reputable Merchant Services<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A payment processor includes a merchant account provided by platform merchant services. When your customer pays with cards or any digital payment method, processors are responsible for transmitting the information.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can set this up with an all-in-one payment service or independent sales organization for assured transaction security.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"easy-to-use-point-of-sales-terminals\"><\/span>Easy-to-Use Point of Sales Terminals<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Point of sales or POS devices enable your customer to insert, tap or swipe their means of payment when purchasing from your business. These gadgets are either bought or hired, and they can be handheld or built into larger terminals or apparatus. With these systems, you stand less risk, which also helps record your sales for inventory keeping.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"all-in-one-payment-service-providers\"><\/span>All in One Payment Service Providers<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>PSPs or payment service providers can help you set up a bundled merchant account and point of sale systems. Although it\u2019s more costly than setting up DIY no-cash payments, it\u2019s easier and more secure.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"payment-gateways-for-online-sales\"><\/span>Payment Gateways for Online Sales<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You must integrate your e-commerce website with a digital payments gateway if you\u2019re an online merchant. That\u2019s what the shopping cart connects to, letting your customers purchase and check out their choices.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some gateways allow you to accept electronic bank transfers and can be sourced from your digital Payments Service Provider or merchant account service.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"do-modern-payment-types-come-embedded-with-corresponding-security-features\"><\/span>Do Modern Payment Types Come Embedded with Corresponding Security Features?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the era of real-time payment types, secure processing of transactions takes centre stage. Biometric technology advances change how security issues are viewed while other protocols verify a user\u2019s identity. These methods secure card-not-present or CNP transactions and include voice, facial, and fingerprint recognition.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Chip card technology fills the gap for card-present transactions to ease communication with contactless terminals or POS devices.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The integrated encryption protects against fraud, while Secure Remote Commerce technology allows merchants to create <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-multiple-payment-gateways-help-merchants-sell\/\">virtual payment terminals<\/a>. SRC protects cardholder information with robust tokenization and can be used remotely on tablets, laptops, or smartphones.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Encryption methods such as TLS and SSL are the standard for securing payment types for the online merchant. You can obtain certification from a hosting service to ensure that your customer\u2019s data is encrypted while securing your site. 3-D gateways offer two-step security authentication for your checkout transactions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A professional payment service provider optimizes these efforts while helping you comply with regulations and industry standards.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"secure-transactions-while-evading-modern-complexity-of-payments\"><\/span>Secure Transactions While Evading Modern Complexity of Payments<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want competitiveness in today\u2019s commercial playground, you must learn to use modern payment types securely. These are an essential part of a positive contemporary user experience for your customers and the best solution for managing your business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, seek the best fit for your business niche according to your user\u2019s expectations instead of embedding all of these methods.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Point Sale scanners are user and customer-friendly, and more efficient fo